profile_positions.description:
DutchBasecamp is a non-profit that connects the startup ecosystems of Silicon Valley and The Netherlands, and strengthens the Dutch startup ecosystem in any way it can. Our goal is for The Netherlands to be thé startup hub in Europe.

Activities range from 
* organizing the "Silicon Valley Fundamentals" - my latest bog on our 1st event: http://dutchbasecamp.org/blog-get-ready/
* organizing "startup bootcamps" for Dutch startups to Silicon Valley/New York and Boston, to strengthen and inspire them, validate their business model and test whether an international expansion is for them; 
* organizing "Executive bootcamps" for Dutch corporates to Silicon Valley to introduce them to the latest innovations by US startups that'll bring them a competitive advantage; 
* creating 'lead partners' for foreign startups that want to locate their operations in The Netherlands, providing them with a pool of corporates that'll act as more than just their launching customers but really become their pártner, in order to help them enter the Dutch market successfully; 
* coordinating a Partners in International Business (PIB) application for Dutch accelerators and incubators to give them a better, solid access into Silicon Valley which will benefit both their portfolio startups as well as their own organization (because of their improved appeal to foreign startups that seek to enter the US market via The Netherlands); 
* organizing intensive "explore camps" for Dutch startups that decide to expand the The Unites States and provide them with a soft landing during the first three months through connections & introductions to mentors and a range of qualified partners.

In summary, we focus on the following 3 things:
- Provide a soft-landing for Dutch start-ups that expand to the United States
- Help fast-growing US companies choose The Netherlands as their hub for expansion into Europe
- Bring the "Silicon Valley mindset" of serial entrepreneurship to the Dutch start-up ecosystem
